OL,3,GDumfries, Galloway, Lothian & Borders
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA chilly, mostly dry and sunny
OL,6,Fstart to the day. Then clouds
OL,7,Fbuilding, perhaps bringing a few light
OL,8,Fshowers, the east then brightening
OL,9,Fagain later.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FLight showers possible for
OL,12,FDumfries and Galloway this evening,
OL,13,Fbut largely dry with late sunny spells
OL,14,Fin the east. Clearing skies overnight
OL,15,Fwill then bring a touch of frost.
OL,16,
OL,17,CWednesday:FA touch of frost first
OL,18,Fthing in the morning for some. It will
OL,19,Fthen be a dry and bright day with a
OL,20,Ffew rather hazy sunny spells between
OL,21,Fpatchy cloud.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
